        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is the difference between an HSIIDC plot and a freehold industrial plot?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "An HSIIDC plot is allotted by the Haryana State Industrial and Infrastructure Development Corporation on long-term lease or conditional transfer, carrying restrictions on use, deadlines for construction and prior approval for sale or mortgage. A freehold industrial plot bought privately carries no such conditions and no allotment price advantage. The conditions attach to the plot, not the buyer."
